---
name: EnsureBranches
description: Rules for branch discipline per feature/change set
alwaysApply: true
---
## Rules

### 1. Use a single git branch for each set of associated changes
Always keep all related edits for one feature/change set in one dedicated branch.

### 2. Never implement feature/change-set work directly on main/master
Always create and switch to a dedicated branch before starting a new feature/change set.

### 3. Create a new discrete branch for unrelated work
When a new request is unrelated to the current branch scope, create a new branch for that request instead of mixing changes.

### 4. Use a clear branch naming convention
Name branches with a scope prefix and short slug, such as `feature/<slug>`, `fix/<slug>`, `docs/<slug>`, or `chore/<slug>`.

### 5. Confirm branch scope before coding
Before substantial edits, verify the current branch matches the requested scope; if not, create/switch branches first.
